'''Janner''' refers to a person from the city of [[Plymouth]] in south-west [[Devon]], and the dialect and accent of that person. '''Janner''' is to [[Plymouth]] what [[Scouse]] is to [[Liverpool]].

Unlike better-known English regional accents like [[Scouse]], [[Geordie]] and [[Cockney#London_speech|Cockney]], Janner is rarely mentioned or recognised outside the Plymouth area. Because of this lack of recognition, little if any research has been undertaken into the [[dialect]] and [[accent]].
